  "text": "Our research group studied the effects of RA supplementation in normal rats. RA supplemented at a physiologic dose, in rats without any type of cardiovascular aggression, caused cardiac remodeling with left ventricular hypertrophy, without interstitial fibrosis, and maintenance of cardiac geometry and function [CITATION_1] . Importantly, this pattern is found in both physiologic (isotonic exercise) and pathologic (compensated volume overload) conditions. We also studied patients using 13-cys-RA for acne treatment [CITATION_2] . These patients showed increase in relative wall thickness and in left ventricle (LV) mass, without changes in cardiac function after 10 weeks of treatment. Thus, the doubt about physiologic or pathologic remodeling induced by RA supplementation still remains. In this manner, this study aimed to discern whether the cardiac alterations caused by RA in normal adult rats are physiologic or pathologic. Therefore, we analyzed the energy metabolism status, oxidative stress condition, and the signaling pathway involved in the cardiac remodeling induced by RA.",
